%% Máquina de Estados: ReactLoop Execution
%% Referência: docs/blueprint/09-state-models.md

stateDiagram-v2
    direction TB

    [*] --> idle

    idle : Loop criado, aguardando execute()
    streaming : Recebendo SSE chunks do OpenRouter
    executing_tools : Executando tool calls (parallel/sequential)
    completed : Texto final entregue
    error : Erro irrecuperável
    cost_limited : CostPolicy atingida
    aborted : Cancelado via AbortSignal

    idle --> streaming : execute() chamado
    streaming --> executing_tools : LLM retorna tool_calls
    streaming --> completed : LLM retorna texto final (stop)
    streaming --> error : OpenRouter falha após retries
    streaming --> cost_limited : maxTokensPerExecution (stop)
    streaming --> aborted : AbortSignal disparado
    executing_tools --> streaming : Tools executadas, próxima iteração
    executing_tools --> error : maxConsecutiveErrors atingido
    executing_tools --> completed : maxIterations atingido
    executing_tools --> aborted : AbortSignal disparado

    completed --> [*]
    error --> [*]
    cost_limited --> [*]
    aborted --> [*]

    note right of streaming
        Emite: turn_start, text_delta
        Verifica cost antes de cada chamada LLM
    end note

    note right of executing_tools
        Emite: tool_call_start, tool_call_end
        onToolError: continue|stop|retry
    end note

    note left of completed
        Emite: text_done, turn_end, agent_end
        Usage acumulado reportado
    end note
